cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM 

This paper deals with the recognition of regular omega languages by deterministic parity acceptors and deterministic Muller acceptors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also describes polynomial time algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithms involve graph theory and automata, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
